snippet.title: Materiality - Accounting Music Video - Love$Accy - Petty Ca$h & Meri Amber
snippet.description:
The ever-so material accounting song you've all been waiting for!! Materiality is an auditor's anthem created by two accounting musicians: Petty Ca$h [rap] & Auditor Meri [lead vocals & music production]. Who says accountants aren't awesome? They are... They truly are the awesomest.

---

Follow Petty Ca$h:
On YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/user/Carricktor
On Twitter: https://twitter.com/carricktor
On Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/carricktor

---

I'd love for you to come hang out with me around the internets at:
My cosy online home - http://www.meriamber.com
Twitch - https://www.twitch.tv/meriamber
Twitter [@meriamber] - http://twitter.com/meriamber
Instagram [@meriamber] - https://instagram.com/meriamber
Facebook - http://www.facebook.com/meriamber
Google+ - https://plus.google.com/+meriamber/posts

And listen to my music on:
My music page - http://www.meriamber.com/music
Spotify - https://play.spotify.com/artist/4ULUypMfEm9tEgWbzsww3b
Apple Music - https://itunes.apple.com/au/artist/meri-amber/id634506373
Google Play - http://bit.ly/MAonGooglePlay
BandCamp - https://meriamber.bandcamp.com

---

If you wanna grab one of my tracks and an e-zine for free, pop by here: http://bit.ly/MAFreeStuff

---

And here's the lyrics, in case you're a word muncher:
So you wanna learn about Materiality?
Well here's your lesson.

I spend every morning waking up eating cereal.
All about that multi-grain, peanut butter Cheerio
I Purell my hands cause I'm anti-bacterial
Point one per cent germs, you know that's immaterial

There's a watch on my wrist, still immaterial
A note that's out of pitch, it's still immaterial
Computer's got a glitch, also immaterial
A broken toggle switch, it must be immaterial

There's water in my boat, still immaterial
There's holes in my coat, still immaterial
A sore in my throat, also immaterial
Went to cast my vote, we know it's immaterial

Go get me a mop cause I'm cleaning up your mess man
Married to accounting but I'd rather be the best man
Passing on investigations, I hope you did the test man
Cause when it comes to waiving well you know that I'm the 'yes' man

Do the checks on what's significant
Check the materiality, materiality
In the end it makes all the difference or not
Materiality, materiality

I'm feeling like a miracle, being all satirical
Trying to copy me with my lyrical material
Faililng the criteria, looks like that's inferior
If my plates not full then I hit the cafeteria

Started on the balance sheet, waived on the financials
Moved on to the income statement, tested all the samples
All of the cash flow items, I don't know the answer
So I'll pass on everything I know they're not substantial

View the television ratings, yeah they're immaterial
Check out all the girls I'm dating, still it's immaterial
Heard of all the things they're saying, always immaterial
Watch me in the games I'm playing, yeah it's immaterial

All the texts I don't respond to, sorry not material
People know what's up, they keep asking what's the deal-io
Petty here with Meri Amber you know it's for real-io
Accounting rap is life so I'll always be material


Do the checks on what's significant
Check the materiality, materiality
In the end it makes all the difference or not
Materiality, materiality

Twenty-thousand bucks
Immaterial
Driving in your truck
Immaterial
A coffee from Starbucks
Immaterial
Claiming this is luck
Immaterial
Phone call from your mum
Immaterial
Some dude who's name is Tom
Immaterial
Found out I'm adopted
Immaterial
The song that I just dropped is
Immaterial

Do the checks on what's significant
Check the materiality, materiality
In the end it makes all the difference or not
Materiality, materiality

Oh think about the bottom line
And the billable hours of your time
And how much effort it takes to type
Under the disclosures

Petty Ca$h boiiiiii
Meri Amber
We footed.

---

Last but not least, the credits:
The song was written by Petty Ca$h and me and produced by me in my home studio. The video was filmed by Petty Ca$h and me separately and edited together by me.

---

Thank you for watching and a huge thank you for subscribing if you've subscribed too!
